body_html: That is interesting. Before the configure script runs the bazel fetch command (where the error is happening), it runs bazel clean --expunge, which should have deleted all of the files Bazel generated for the workspace. Is it possible that not all of the files were deleted?

body: That is interesting. Before the `configure` script runs the `bazel fetch` command (where the error is happening), it runs `bazel clean --expunge`, which should have deleted all of the files Bazel generated for the workspace. Is it possible that not all of the files were deleted?
